&lt;p&gt;Kakigori is a dessert, a giant mound of shaved ice, generally flavored with syrup or fruit; but tea, coffee, nuts, chocolate... the sky is the limit. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the hands of the best chefs, it’s more like eating freshly fallen snow; fluffy, not crunchy; refreshing!
&lt;/p&gt;
